			        <td valign="top" class="tableCell"><span id="speakerTitleCompanyLabel">President and CEO, Stormfront Studios</span></td>
		        </tr>
		        <tr>
			        <td valign="top" class="tableCell"><span id="speakerBioLabel">Don L. Daglow has served as president and CEO of Stormfront Studios since founding the company in 1988.  Stormfront's many hit titles include The Lord of the Rings: The Two Towers (PS2/Xbox), the creation of the NASCAR Racing franchise for EA Sports, and the first graphical MMORPG, the original Neverwinter Nights.  In 2003 he received the CGE Achievement Award for “groundbreaking accomplishments that shaped the Video Game Industry.”  Don previously served as director of Intellivision game development for Mattel, as a producer at Electronic Arts, and as an executive at Broderbund.  He designed the first computer baseball game (1971), the first computer RPG (Dungeon, 1975), the first sim game (Intellivision Utopia, 1981), and the first game to use multiple camera angles (Intellivision World Series Baseball, 1983).  He serves on the Board of Directors of the Academy of Interactive Arts and Sciences.</span></td>
